    "\n",
    "    * The Saturation: The dense saturation between 18°C and 24°C both above and below the line shows that Kenya’s weather is highly stable. This is the \"Equatorial Sweet Spot\" where the proximity to the Indian Ocean keeps the climate from swinging into extreme dry heat.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. Temperature vs. Wind Speed: The Trade Wind Signature\n",
    "\n",
    "    * The Trend: An upward slope from (4°C,2m/s) to (20°C,3.8m/s) captures the relationship between heat and air movement.\n",
    "\n",
